Name: Particle_Parameter
Description: The Particle_Parameter class contains metadata identifying specific particle science parameters.

Name: particle_type
Description: The particle_type attribute indicates the type of particle being described.

Name: Electrons
Description: Electrons are subatomic particles with a negative electrical charge.

Name: Ions
Description: Ions are particles with an electrical charge.

Name: Neutrals
Description: Neutrals are particles with no net electrical charge.

Name: particle_measurement_type
Description: The particle_measurement_type attribute indicates the type of particle measurement parameters.

Name: Composition
Description: Distribution of particle types

Name: Count Rate
Description: Particle detections per accumulation interval

Name: Counts
Description: Sensor particle detections (may include both raw and corrected counts)

Name: Current
Description: Current produced by particle impacts on detector

Name: Density
Description: Particle number or mass density

Name: Density Profile
Description: Particle density by altitude

Name: Distribution Function
Description: Particle distribution

Name: Dynamic Pressure
Description: Pressure due to the kinetic motion of the particles

Name: Energy Flux
Description: Particle energy per unit area per time. This value should be used for differential and integral energy flux as well.

Name: Energy Spectra
Description: Particle distribution of energy

Name: Flux
Description: Particle detections per time per area

Name: Mass Spectra
Description: Particle distribution of mass-to-charge ratio

Name: Pitch Angle Distribution
Description: Particle distribution organized by magnetic-field direction

Name: Pulse Height Analysis
Description: Particle energy spectra over a specified time interval

Name: Temperature
Description: Particle distribution temperature

Name: Thermal Pressure
Description: Pressure due to the thermal motion of the particles

Name: Time of Flight
Description: Particle mass distribution determined by particle's measured momentum and time it take to travel between two sensors

Name: Velocity
Description: Particle bulk or vector velocity

Name: ion_type
Description: The ion_type attribute indicates the types of ions measured.

Name: Alpha
Description: Positively charged particle consisting of two protons and two neutrons

Name: Heavy
Description: Ions with a higher atomic number than helium

Name: Proton
Description: Positively charged subatomic particle

Name: Particle_Observation
Description: The Particle_Observation class is the container for particle discipline related metadata elements.

Name: energy_range_minimum
Description: The energy_range_minimum attribute indicates the lowest measured energy for the described particle_type.

Name: energy_range_maximum
Description: The energy_range_minimum attribute indicates the highest measured energy for the described particle_type.
